                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra (name of God in Texts I-1, I-2 and I-3;
                           name of St Mary and other names in Texts I-4, I-5 and I-6; titles and
                           numbers of the Pss., Canticles and Songs; titel of Texts I-2, I-3, I-5,
                           I-6; title and incipit of the daily readings of Text I-4; name, number
                           and traditional interpretation of the Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; a few
                           single words in Texts I-4, I-5, I-6; elements of the punctuation signs
                           and text dividers.
 
 A few groups of lines (alternating with
                           black lines) on the incipit page of Texts I-1 and I-4; two lines
                           (alternating with a black line) of the incipit of each Ps., Canticle and
                           Song.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>: Crude uncoloured ornamental band; geometric
                        motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>: Crude uncoloured ornamental band; geometric
                        motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#3v">Fol. 3v: </locus>
                        <desc>Priest (the donor?) presenting a Psalter to St. Mary, a woman (the
                           donor´s wife?).</desc>The title of the book መዝሙር፡ ዘዳዊት and the initial
                        line of Ps. 1, ፈካርየ፡ ዘጻድ[ቃ]ን፡ ወዘሐጥኣ[ን], are readable.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#4r">Fol. 4r: </locus>
                        <desc>The Virgin and Child.</desc>The miniature is protected by a textile
                        curtain.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>List of the feasts dedicated to St Mary.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: ኅልቈ፡ በአላቲሃ፡ ለእግዝትነ፡ ማርያም፡...</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand as Additiones 2 and 3.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r-v</locus>
                           <desc>List of the feasts dedicated to the Apostles.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: ወካዕበ፡ እጽሕፍ፡ ሕልቈ፡ በዓላቲሆሙ፡
                              ለሐዋርያት፡…</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in the same hand as Additiones 1 and 3.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>Genealogy starting with a certain Gabra Krǝstos.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am">
                              <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>: ሕልቈ፡ ትወልድ፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልደ፡ ክርስቶስ፡
                              ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም፡...</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic, in the same hand as Additiones 1
                              and 2. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#152v">f. 152v</locus>
                           <desc>Genealogy of an unknown person starting from King Solomon of
                              Israel and Mǝnilǝk I.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic. The first name in the genealogy
                              has been erased. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten by means of a
                           chain of red and black dots.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>- The scribe reduced the size of his
                           handwriting to accommodate the end of the line: e.g., <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 6r, 6v, 7v, 8v, 9v, 10r, 10v, 11v, etc.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc> - Part of
                           the line is taken up: <locus target="#32v">32v</locus>, 44r, 48r, 55r,
                                 73v, 87r, 93r, 94r, 97v, 102v, 104r, 121v.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc> - Tamallas-sign, in the
                           shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the place where the
                           omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: <locus target="#150vb">150vb</locus> l.16, 151ra l.1.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc> - Omitted letters, words, lines
                           or passages written interlineally, in the main and in secondary hands:
                           e.g., <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 6v, 8r, 15v, 26v, 29r, 32v, 36r,
                                 43v, 51v, 56v, 60v, 73r, 115r, 132v, 136r, 145vab.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc> - Corrections
                           over erasures: <locus target="#22r">22r</locus>, 86r, 93v, 101v,
